# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
# combined — __rand__, __ror__, __rxor__ across all 6 decimal subjects
#
# 6 classes x 3 methods = 18 rows.
# All eighteen values are false; Decimal does not define reflected bitwise
# logical operators (__rand__, __ror__, __rxor__) because it is an IEEE 754
# decimal floating-point type without bitwise semantics, consistent with
# wave 661 where the forward operators __and__, __or__, __xor__ were all
# false for Decimal. All other decimal classes define none of the three.
# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------

